liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Armed group Hezbollah claimed responsibility for a rocket and artillery attack on the Israeli-occupied Shebaa Farms on Sunday, saying it was "in solidarity" with the Palestinian people. The group said in a written statement cited by Reuters that the attack targeted three posts including a "radar site" in the Shebaa Farms, a slice of land occupied by Israel since 1967 that Lebanon has claimed as its own. As reported earlier, Israel responded on Sunday with artillery fire on southern Lebanon. Israel's military said one its drones struck a Hezbollah post in the area of Har Dov, an area in Shebaa. There have so far been no reports of casualties. Chebaa Farms was captured by Israel from Syria during the 1967 Mideast war, but Lebanon considers it and the nearby Kfar Chouba hills as Lebanese territories. The Golan Heights were annexed by Israel in 1981.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Hezbollah claims responsibility for attack on Israeli-occupied Shebaa farms

children.content: Armed group Hezbollah claimed responsibility for a rocket and artillery attack on the Israeli-occupied Shebaa Farms on Sunday, saying it was "in solidarity" with the Palestinian people.

The group said in a written statement cited by Reuters that the attack targeted three posts including a "radar site" in the Shebaa Farms, a slice of land occupied by Israel since 1967 that Lebanon has claimed as its own.
As reported earlier, Israel responded on Sunday with artillery fire on southern Lebanon.
Israel's military said one its drones struck a Hezbollah post in the area of Har Dov, an area in Shebaa.
There have so far been no reports of casualties.
Chebaa Farms was captured by Israel from Syria during the 1967 Mideast war, but Lebanon considers it and the nearby Kfar Chouba hills as Lebanese territories.
The Golan Heights were annexed by Israel in 1981.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: This is something analysts have said could constitute an escalation, but at this stage, the cross-border military fire is contained to the area that is very much contested by Hezbollah. Earlier, Reuters reported mortar fire from inside Lebanon into northern Israel. Now the agency is reporting the Israeli military has fired back. "IDF artillery is currently striking the area in Lebanon from where a shooting was carried out," Israeli forces announced. Security sources told Reuters projectiles launched from Lebanese territory hit an Israeli military position in the Israeli-occupied Shebaa farms early on Sunday. The sources said Israeli artillery fire then began hitting Lebanese territory.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Artillery fired over Lebanon-Israel border in the north
